# Build and Test On Every Code Change

Whenever code changes are made, run build/typecheck and tests for the impacted area.
This is mandatory for every change batch, not only before final completion.

## Required checks

- Run a build/typecheck command for impacted packages/apps immediately after the change.
- Run tests for impacted packages/apps immediately after the change.
- If full-repo checks are too expensive, run targeted checks that cover edited areas and state exactly what was run.

## Enforcement (always)

- Run build/typecheck + tests immediately after each code change batch.
- Do not proceed as if work is complete for that batch until both checks pass.
- Do not claim success or "done" status unless the latest build and test run passed for the changed scope.
- If build or tests fail, fix issues and re-run both checks.
- Always summarize the commands run and their outcomes.

## Example

```bash
pnpm turbo run typecheck --filter=@sm/web --filter=@sm/api
pnpm turbo run test --filter=@sm/web --filter=@sm/api
```
